<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY:

 In response to a recommendation by the National Performance Review, this proposed revision to the grants management
common rule, ``Uniform Administrative Requirements for Grants and Cooperative Agreements to State and Local Governments,''
originally issued in the March 11, 1988, 

Federal Register

, is issued to raise the dollar threshold for simplified procedures for small purchases (simplified acquisition
threshold) by State and local grantees. The agencies' common rule provides uniform fiscal and administrative requirements
applicable to all types of grants and cooperative agreements to State and local governments. 


